About: The Agtech Incentive Scheme is part of an accelerator program to establish the UAE’s capital as a global center for agricultural innovation in desert environments. The UAE Government will offer a series of cash and non-cash incentives to make it easier for local and global agtech companies to set up and expand their operations. The incentive packages will enable the creation of advanced agtech knowledge in Abu Dhabi and help to solve traditional farming challenges. The package is part of Ghadan 21 (Tomorrow 21), which is a three-year AED 50 billion programme designed to accelerate the capital’s economic growth.
title: ADIO Agtech Incentive Scheme

About: Dubai Future Accelerators facilitates collaboration between government entities and private sector organizations from around the world to co-create solutions for bold challenges of tomorrow. About: Smartpreneur Competition is an open competition for technology startups who have solutions in the fields of sustainability, mobility, and opportunity. The competition seeks innovative solutions in alternative food sources, water, and renewable and clean energy that will contribute to preserving our environment in alignment with UAE Green Economy Vision 2021. Participants who qualify will attend two full-day workshops on mentorship, relationship-building, and business plan development.
title: Smartpreneur Competition

About: The Mohammed bin Rashid Initiative for Global Prosperity invites the world’s leading manufacturers, start-ups and entrepreneurs, governments, UN agencies and philanthropists, academia and researchers, to form a community dedicated to spreading global prosperity through the art of ‘making’. The initiative specifically seeks to recognize achievements that have positively contributed to the well-being of our world while fostering the values of resilience, community, harmony and dignity. The initiative is organized into 4 themes every year. Previous themes include "Sustainable and Healthy Food for All" and "Rural Transformation and Zero Hunger".
title: MBR Global Makers Challenge

About: ShjSEEN is a program from the Sharjah Chamber of Commerce & Industry that offers a total of 7 different awards to businesses that promote entrepreneurship in the emirate. ShjSeen aims to benefit Sharjah’s economy in all business sectors by furthering sustainable economic growth and recognizing business achievement.
title: ShjSEEN Awards Programme

About: The Khalifa International Award for Date Palm and Agriculture Innovation aims to recognize individuals and organizations dedicated to increasing agricultural productivity in the UAE.

About: Zayed Sustainability Prize is the UAE´s pioneering global award in sustainability and a tribute to the legacy of the late founding father of the UAE, Sheikh Zayed bin Sultan al Nahyan. Established in 2008, this annual award recognizes and rewards the achievements of those who are driving impactful, innovative and inspiring sustainability solutions across five distinct categories: Health, Food, Energy, Water and Global High Schools.
title: Zayed Sustainability Prize

About:
The Global Forum for Innovations in Agriculture (GFIA) are designed to celebrate innovations that help to improve global food security without destroying our planet. Award categories:
Best innovation in honey production
Best indoor farming innovation
Best innovation in animal production
Best aquaculture innovation
Best date production innovation
Best innovation in crops production
Best innovation by a start-up company
title: Global Forum for Innovations in Agriculture (GFIA)

About: The group seeks to explore plant biological and physiological processes, and understand the ecological complexity of desert ecosystems. The priority of the group is to establish a molecular physiology lab that could help in defining candidate genes that help plants tolerate the harsh conditions of the UAE deserts.
title: University of Sharjah – Environmental and Chemical Biology Research Group

About: The Sustainable Bioenergy Research Consortium (SBRC) is a research center that aims to advance the aviation industry’s commitment to sustainable business practices by developing technology with the promise of producing a clean, alternative fuel supply. The Seawater Energy and Agriculture System (SEAS) is the flagship project of the SBRC. This project combines an integrated system of aquaculture, halo-agriculture, and halo-agroforestry to produce sustainable biofuels for aviation and seafood.
title: Khalifa University – Sustainable Bioenergy Research Consortium (SBRC)

About: The UAEU University College of Food and Agriculture is an interdisciplinary program that studies advanced food technology systems, such as production agriculture, food processing, agribusiness and natural resources, and the environment. The College consists of 3 departments: Department of Integrative Agriculture, Department of Food, Nutrition and Health, and Department of Veterinary Medicine.
title: UAEU College of Food and Agriculture

About: The Date Palm Research and Development Unit at UAE University is a research laboratory that studies how to increase agricultural productivity in date palms, a significant product in the country. One of these projects is the Date Palm Tissue Culture Laboratory, which experiments with different kinds of in vitro propagation of date palms.
title: UAEU Date Palm Research and Development Unit

About: The Emirates Center for Energy and Environment Research (ECEER) is a research center on energy production and environmental issues by providing analyses, research and technical solutions with particular emphasis on the UAE and regional energy issues. It focuses on 6 key research areas that include oil and gas, petrochemicals, environment, alternative sources and efficient use of energy, energy studies & policies and energy utilization and efficiency.
title: UAEU Emirates Center for Energy and Environment Research

About: The research at the KCGEB is involved in the development of crops tolerant to abiotic stresses through knowledge generation and translational research. The Center is also focused on developing crops with enhanced agronomic traits to expand value chains of existing industrial crops through genomics, genetic engineering and biotechnological innovations.
title: UAEU Khalifa Center for Genetic Engineering and Biotechnology

About: The National Water Center (NWC) is a multidisciplinary research and consultancy center based at UAE University in Al Ain. Its scope of research encompasses assessment, development, management and sustainability of groundwater, surface water, desalinated water, and treated wastewater. The Center provides high-impact research and innovative practical solutions to water-related challenges across the United Arab Emirates and beyond.
title: UAEU National Water Center

About:
The UAE Government is organising the World Virtual GovHack, which invites top minds from around the world to team up and help in producing innovative solutions that would benefit the global community in the following key challenges:
Refugee resettlement
Clean water
Food security
Electricity access
Economic security
Government services transformation
title: GovTech Prize
